asad Saksena |author-link=Banarsi Prasad Saksena |chapter=The Khaljis: Alauddin Khalji |editor=Mohammad Habib and Khaliq Ahmad Nizami |title=A Comprehensive History of India: The Delhi Sultanat (A.D. 1206-1526) |volume=5 |edition=Second |year=1992 |orig-year=1970 |publisher=The Indian History Congress / People's Publishing House |url=https://books.google.com/?id=_9cmAQAAMAAJ |oclc=31870180 |ref=harv }}\n* {{cite book |author=Satish Chandra |author-link=Satish Chandra |title=History of Medieval India: 800-1700 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=qHnHHwAACAAJ |year=2007 |publisher=Orient Longman |isbn=978-81-250-3226-7 |ref=harv }}\n{{ref end}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category}}\n{{wikiquote}}\n\n{{Turkic topics|state=collapsed}}\n{{Authority control}}\n[[Category:Historical Turkic states]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in 1206]]\n[[Category:Delhi Sultanate| ]]\n[[Category:Empires and kingdoms of India]]\n[[Category:Former sultanates]]\n[[Category:Islamic rule in the Indian subcontinent]]\n[[Category:1206 establishments in Asia]]\n[[Category:13th-century establishments in India]]\n[[Category:1526 disestablishments in India]]\n[[Category:States and territories disestablished in 1526]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|Sultanate of Deli}}\n{{short description|Successive Islamic dynasties that ruled large parts of the Indian subcontinent (1206\u20131526)}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=June 2013}}{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}}\n{{Infobox country\n| conventional_long_name                = Delhi Sultanate\n| native_name                = {{lang|fa|Chirag}}\n| common_name                = Delhi Sultanate\n| image_flag                = Delhi Sultanate Flag.svg\n| era                = Middle Ages\n| event_start                = [[History of Delhi#8th century to 16th century|Independence]]<ref name=\"Jackson2003\">{{cite book|last=Jackson|first=Peter|title=The Delhi Sultanate: A Political and Military History|url=https://books.google.com/?id=lt2tqOpVRKg